{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839630007,"sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784a4df80010TR7WRNFONv8DC","messageID":"msg_d784a37d70013DuK9FfzdEfGND","sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_511f0cef88f74cb1b0105330","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD type implementations including Go API types, CRD manifests, client-go library, informers, and listers for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n6: \n7: ## Requirements\n8: \n9: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime API type definition\n10: \n11: The system SHALL define `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` with `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeSpec` types. `AgentRuntimeSpec` SHALL include `sandboxImage` (string), `tools` ([]Tool), `resources` (ResourceRequirements), `timeout` (metav1.Duration), and `securityContext` (SecurityContext). `AgentRuntime` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`.\n12: \n13: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime type registration\n14: \n15: - **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n16: - **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&AgentRuntime{}, &AgentRuntimeList{})` is called during init\n17: - **THEN** `AgentRuntime` SHALL be registered in the scheme with `Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"`, `APIVersion = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\"`\n18: \n19: #### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec with sandbox image\n20: \n21: - **GIVEN** an `AgentRuntime` YAML with `spec.sandboxImage: \"volcano.sh/agent-sandbox:latest\"`\n22: - **WHEN** the object is parsed by the scheme\n23: - **THEN** `AgentRuntime.Spec.SandboxImage` SHALL be populated with the image string\n24: \n25: #### Scenario: Tool configuration\n26: \n27: - **GIVEN** `spec.tools` contains entries with `name`, `command`, and `args`\n28: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime is deserialized\n29: - **THEN** each tool SHALL have `Name` (string), `Command` ([]string), and `Args` ([]string) populated\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Resource requirements\n32: \n33: - **GIVEN** `spec.resources` specifies `requests` and `limits` for CPU/memory\n34: - **WHEN** the AgentRuntime is validated by the scheme\n35: - **THEN** `Resources` SHALL be of type `corev1.ResourceRequirements` and pass Kubernetes validation\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: AgentRuntime status subresource\n38: \n39: The system SHALL define `AgentRuntimeStatus` with `Phase` (string), `Conditions` ([]metav1.Condition), `SandboxRef` (*corev1.ObjectReference), and `LastTransitionTime` (metav1.Time). `AgentRuntime` SHALL expose `.status` via the status subresource.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Status phase transitions\n42: \n43: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `status.phase = \"Pending\"`\n44: - **WHEN** the controller updates status to `\"Running\"`\n45: - **THEN** `LastTransitionTime` SHALL be updated and a new Condition added to `Conditions`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Condition management\n48: \n49: - **GIVEN** a condition of type `\"Ready\"` with `status: \"True\"`, `reason: \"SandboxReady\"`, `message: \"Sandbox is running\"`\n50: - **WHEN** status is updated via the status subresource\n51: - **THEN** the condition SHALL be upserted into `status.conditions` with `lastTransitionTime` set\n52: \n53: #### Scenario: Sandbox reference\n54: \n55: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod is created for this AgentRuntime\n56: - **WHEN** the controller sets `status.sandboxRef` to the pod's ObjectReference\n57: - **THEN** `sandboxRef` SHALL contain `name`, `namespace`, `uid`, and `apiVersion` of the sandbox\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: CodeInterpreter API type definition\n60: \n61: The system SHALL define `CodeInterpreter` and `CodeInterpreterSpec` in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types.go`. `CodeInterpreterSpec` SHALL include `runtimeRef` (string), `code` (string), `language` (string), and `executionPolicy` (ExecutionPolicy).\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: CodeInterpreter type registration\n64: \n65: - **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n66: - **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&CodeInterpreter{}, &CodeInterpreterList{})` is called\n67: - **THEN** `CodeInterpreter` SHALL be registered with `Kind = \"CodeInterpreter\"`\n68: \n69: #### Scenario: Runtime reference binding\n70: \n71: - **GIVEN** `spec.runtimeRef: \"python-3.11\"`\n72: - **WHEN** a CodeInterpreter is created\n73: - **THEN** it SHALL reference an AgentRuntime named `python-3.11` in the same namespace\n74: \n75: #### Scenario: Execution policy\n76: \n77: - **GIVEN** `spec.executionPolicy` with `timeout: \"30s\"` and `maxMemory: \"512Mi\"`\n78: - **WHEN** the CodeInterpreter is parsed\n79: - **THEN** `ExecutionPolicy.Timeout` and `ExecutionPolicy.MaxMemory` SHALL be populated\n80: \n81: ### Requirement: CRD manifests generation\n82: \n83: The system SHALL generate `manifests/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` and `manifests/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` via `make gen-crd` using controller-gen.\n84: \n85: #### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD with status subresource\n86: \n87: - **GIVEN** `+genclient` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers on `AgentRuntime`\n88: - **WHEN** `make gen-crd` runs controller-gen\n89: - **THEN** the CRD manifest SHALL include `spec.subresources.status: {}`\n90: \n91: #### Scenario: CRD schema validation\n92: \n93: - **GIVEN** `+kubebuilder:validation:Required` markers on spec fields\n94: - **WHEN** CRDs are generated\n95: - **THEN** the OpenAPI v3 schema SHALL mark those fields as required and specify types\n96: \n97: #### Scenario: CRD group and version\n98: \n99: - **GIVEN** `SchemeGroupVersion = schema.GroupVersion{Group: \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\", Version: \"v1alpha1\"}`\n100: - **WHEN** CRDs render\n101: - **THEN** `metadata.name` SHALL be `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` and `spec.group = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"`\n102: \n103: ### Requirement: client-go typed client generation\n104: \n105: The system SHALL generate typed clients under `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/` with `AgentRuntimeInterface` providing CRUD operations.\n106: \n107: #### Scenario: Create AgentRuntime via typed client\n108: \n109: - **GIVEN** a configured `Clientset` and valid `AgentRuntime` object\n110: - **WHEN** `clientset.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Create(ctx, ar, metav1.CreateOptions{})` is called\n111: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be created via the K8s API and returned with populated metadata\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Update status via typed client\n114: \n115: - **GIVEN** an existing AgentRuntime with a mutable status\n116: - **WHEN** `UpdateStatus(ctx, ar, metav1.UpdateOptions{})` is called\n117: - **THEN** only the status subresource SHALL be updated\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: List with label selector\n120: \n121: - **GIVEN** AgentRuntimes with labels `app=sandbox` in namespace `default`\n122: - **WHEN** `List(ctx, metav1.ListOptions{LabelSelector: \"app=sandbox\"})` is called\n123: - **THEN** only matching AgentRuntimes SHALL be returned\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Watch for changes\n126: \n127: - **GIVEN** a watch on `AgentRuntimes(\"default\")`\n128: - **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created or updated\n129: - **THEN** the watch channel SHALL receive an `Event` with `Type` and `Object`\n130: \n131: ### Requirement: Informer factory generation\n132: \n133: The system SHALL generate `SharedInformerFactory` under `client-go/informers/externalversions/` with `Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes()` and `CodeInterpreters()` accessors.\n134: \n135: #### Scenario: Start informer for AgentRuntimes\n136: \n137: - **GIVEN** a configured `SharedInformerFactory`\n138: - **WHEN** `factory.Runtime().V1alpha1().AgentRuntimes().Informer()` is called and `factory.Start(stopCh)` runs\n139: - **THEN** the informer SHALL list-watch `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` and populate its cache\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Event handlers\n142: \n143: - **GIVEN** an informer with `AddEventHandler` registered\n144: - **WHEN** an AgentRuntime is created\n145: - **THEN** the `OnAdd` callback SHALL be invoked with the new object\n146: \n147: #### Scenario: Namespace-filtered informer\n148: \n149: - **GIVEN** `NewFilteredSharedInformerFactory` with namespace `production`\n150: - **WHEN** the factory starts\n151: - **THEN** the informer SHALL only watch AgentRuntimes in `production` namespace\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: Lister generation\n154: \n155: The system SHALL generate `AgentRuntimeLister` and `AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister` under `client-go/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/` with `List(selector)` and `Get(name)` methods.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: List all AgentRuntimes\n158: \n159: - **GIVEN** a populated informer cache\n160: - **WHEN** `lister.List(labels.Everything())` is called\n161: - **THEN** all AgentRuntimes SHALL be returned from the cache\n162: \n163: #### Scenario: Get by name and namespace\n164: \n165: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime named `sandbox-1` in namespace `default` exists in cache\n166: - **WHEN** `lister.AgentRuntimes(\"default\").Get(\"sandbox-1\")` is called\n167: - **THEN** the AgentRuntime SHALL be returned or `NotFound` error if absent\n168: \n169: ### Requirement: Fake clients for testing\n170: \n171: The system SHALL generate fake clients under `client-go/clientset/versioned/fake/` and `client-go/clientset/versioned/typed/runtime/v1alpha1/fake/` implementing the typed interfaces.\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Unit test with fake client\n174: \n175: - **GIVEN** `fake.NewSimpleClientset()` is called\n176: - **WHEN** `Create`, `Get`, `Update`, `Delete` are called on the fake client\n177: - **THEN** operations SHALL succeed in-memory without contacting K8s API\n178: \n179: #### Scenario: Reactor for error injection\n180: \n181: - **GIVEN** a fake client with `PrependReactor(\"create\", \"agentruntimes\", ...)` that returns an error\n182: - **WHEN** `Create` is called\n183: - **THEN** the reactor SHALL intercept and return the injected error\n184: \n185: ### Requirement: Scheme and codec registration\n186: \n187: The system SHALL register types in `client-go/clientset/versioned/scheme/register.go` with `AddToScheme` functions for the generated client.\n188: \n189: #### Scenario: Scheme registration at client init\n190: \n191: - **GIVEN** the `client-go` package is imported\n192: - **WHEN** `scheme.AddToScheme(runtimeScheme)` is called\n193: - **THEN** `AgentRuntime` and `CodeInterpreter` types SHALL be recognizable by the scheme\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Negotiated serializer\n196: \n197: - **GIVEN** a REST client with `NegotiatedSerializer`\n198: - **WHEN** encoding/decoding is needed\n199: - **THEN** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` SHALL be supported with `application/json`\n\n(End of file - total 199 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Delta Specification\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRD type implementations including Go API types, CRD manifests, client-go library, informers, and listers for the `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` API group.\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: AgentRuntime API type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go` with `AgentRuntime` and `AgentRuntimeSpec` types. `AgentRuntimeSpec` SHALL include `sandboxImage` (string), `tools` ([]Tool), `resources` (ResourceRequirements), `timeout` (metav1.Duration), and `securityContext` (SecurityContext). `AgentRuntime` SHALL embed `metav1.TypeMeta` and `metav1.ObjectMeta`.\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime type registration\n\n- **GIVEN** the `v1alpha1` package is imported\n- **WHEN** `SchemeBuilder.Register(&AgentRuntime{}, &AgentRuntimeList{})` is called during init\n- **THEN** `AgentRuntime` SHALL be registered in the scheme with `Kind = \"AgentRuntime\"`, `APIVersion = \"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1\"`\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntimeSpec with sandbox image\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775839629994,"end":1775839630005}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839630010,"sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784a438a001wL3C2l9fgrgTu7","messageID":"msg_d784a37d70013DuK9FfzdEfGND","sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_5efda8aee9c041658535cb9d","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/README.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S\n6: \n7: ## Summary\n8: \n9: Define the CRD (Custom Resource Definition) types for AgentRuntime in the pkg/apis module.\n10: \n11: ## Status\n12: \n13: - [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n14: - [ ] Define AgentRuntime CRD types\n15: - [ ] Add Go type definitions\n16: - [ ] Generate CRD manifests\n17: - [ ] Add unit tests\n18: \n19: ## Notes\n20: \n21: See `notes/` directory for implementation notes and decisions.\n22: \n23: ## Source Files\n24: \n25: See `src/` directory for source code changes.\n\n(End of file - total 25 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S\n\n## Summary\n\nDefine the CRD (Custom Resource Definition) types for AgentRuntime in the pkg/apis module.\n\n## Status\n\n- [ ] Scaffold directory structure\n- [ ] Define AgentRuntime CRD types\n- [ ] Add Go type definitions\n- [ ] Generate CRD manifests\n- [ ] Add unit tests\n\n## Notes\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/README.md","time":{"start":1775839629989,"end":1775839630009}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839630013,"sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784a487b001056T7CaEJY5SnU","messageID":"msg_d784a37d70013DuK9FfzdEfGND","sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_7de23f3a28f0400ea2d8fcc3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** pkg/apis  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: Scaffold & Registration\n11: \n12: - [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n13: - [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` - register API group\n14: - [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` - define `SchemeGroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`\n15: - [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` - add Go package documentation\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Phase 2: Type Definitions\n20: \n21: - [ ] **2.1** Define `AgentRuntimePhase` enum (Pending, Running, Failed, Terminating)\n22: - [ ] **2.2** Define `AgentRuntimeCondition` struct (type, status, reason, message, lastTransitionTime)\n23: - [ ] **2.3** Define `CodeInterpreterSpec` struct (enabled, image, resources)\n24: - [ ] **2.4** Define `ResourceQuota` struct (cpu, memory, storage limits)\n25: - [ ] **2.5** Define `NetworkPolicy` struct (egressRules, ingressRules)\n26: - [ ] **2.6** Define `LifecycleHook` struct (preStart, postStop handlers)\n27: - [ ] **2.7** Define `AgentRuntimeSpec` struct (container, resources, network, lifecycle, codeInterpreter)\n28: - [ ] **2.8** Define `AgentRuntimeStatus` struct (phase, conditions, sandboxRef, startTime, lastTransitionTime)\n29: - [ ] **2.9** Define `AgentRuntime` struct (TypeMeta, ObjectMeta, Spec, Status)\n30: - [ ] **2.10** Define `AgentRuntimeList` struct (TypeMeta, ListMeta, Items)\n31: - [ ] **2.11** Add JSON tags (camelCase) and protobuf tags to all types\n32: - [ ] **2.12** Implement `runtime.Object` interface for AgentRuntime and AgentRuntimeList\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## Phase 3: Defaults & Validation\n37: \n38: - [ ] **3.1** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults.go`\n39: - [ ] **3.2** Implement `SetDefaults_AgentRuntime` - set default phase to Pending, default resources if unspecified\n40: - [ ] **3.3** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation.go`\n41: - [ ] **3.4** Implement `ValidateAgentRuntime` - validate spec fields (resource values, image format, hook URLs)\n42: - [ ] **3.5** Implement `ValidateAgentRuntimeStatusUpdate` - validate status transitions and field immutability\n43: \n44: ---\n45: \n46: ## Phase 4: CRD Manifest Generation\n47: \n48: - [ ] **4.1** Add `+genclient` and `+k8s:deepcopy-gen` markers to type definitions\n49: - [ ] **4.2** Add `+kubebuilder:object:root=true` and `+kubebuilder:subresource:status` markers\n50: - [ ] **4.3** Add `+kubebuilder:printcolumn` markers for kubectl output (NAME, PHASE, SANDBOX, AGE)\n51: - [ ] **4.4** Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen) to generate CRD YAML\n52: - [ ] **4.5** Verify generated manifest at `manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`\n53: - [ ] **4.6** Validate OpenAPI v3 schema in generated CRD\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## Phase 5: Client Code Generation\n58: \n59: - [ ] **5.1** Update `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` if needed\n60: - [ ] **5.2** Update `hack/update-codegen.sh` with API group info\n61: - [ ] **5.3** Run `make gen-client` to generate clientset, listers, informers\n62: - [ ] **5.4** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/clientset/versioned/`\n63: - [ ] **5.5** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/listers/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n64: - [ ] **5.6** Verify generated code compiles: `pkg/client/informers/externalversions/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ## Phase 6: Unit Tests\n69: \n70: - [ ] **6.1** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types_test.go`\n71: - [ ] **6.2** Test type round-trip serialization (Go → JSON → Go)\n72: - [ ] **6.3** Test `SetDefaults_AgentRuntime` behavior\n73: - [ ] **6.4** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/validation_test.go`\n74: - [ ] **6.5** Test valid AgentRuntime specs pass validation\n75: - [ ] **6.6** Test invalid specs fail validation (negative resources, invalid image names)\n76: - [ ] **6.7** Test status update validation (phase transitions, immutable fields)\n77: - [ ] **6.8** Test `AddToScheme` registration works correctly\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## Phase 7: Integration & Verification\n82: \n83: - [ ] **7.1** Run `make test` - all unit tests pass\n84: - [ ] **7.2** Run `make verify` - code generation is up to date\n85: - [ ] **7.3** Apply CRD to test cluster: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`\n86: - [ ] **7.4** Verify `kubectl get agentruntime` shows custom columns\n87: - [ ] **7.5** Create sample AgentRuntime YAML in `examples/agentruntime.yaml`\n88: - [ ] **7.6** Apply sample and verify resource is created\n89: - [ ] **7.7** Verify Go client can create/get/update AgentRuntime resources\n90: \n91: ---\n92: \n93: ## Verification Checklist\n94: \n95: - [ ] All Go code compiles without errors\n96: - [ ] `go test ./pkg/apis/runtime/...` passes with ≥80% coverage\n97: - [ ] CRD manifest validates with `kubeval` or `kubectl --dry-run=server`\n98: - [ ] Generated client code is up to date (`git diff` shows no changes after `make gen-client`)\n99: - [ ] Example YAML applies successfully to test cluster\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## Dependencies\n104: \n105: | Task | Depends On |\n106: |------|------------|\n107: | Phase 2 | Phase 1 |\n108: | Phase 3 | Phase 2 |\n109: | Phase 4 | Phase 2 |\n110: | Phase 5 | Phase 4 |\n111: | Phase 6 | Phase 2, 3 |\n112: | Phase 7 | Phase 4, 5, 6 |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## References\n117: \n118: - Proposal: `changes/AR-001/proposal.md`\n119: - Implementation Plan: `proposal.md#implementation-plan`\n120: - Success Criteria: `proposal.md#success-criteria`\n121: - API Conventions: `https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md`\n\n(End of file - total 121 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义 Tasks\n\n**Module:** pkg/apis  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (Design completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Scaffold & Registration\n\n- [ ] **1.1** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` directory structure\n- [ ] **1.2** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` - register API group\n- [ ] **1.3** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go` - define `SchemeGroupVersion`, `SchemeBuilder`, `AddToScheme`\n- [ ] **1.4** Create `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/doc.go` - add Go package documentation\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Type Definitions\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775839629992,"end":1775839630011}}}}
