{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839635612,"sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784a628d001FgLcQoEcjx1Wh3","messageID":"msg_d784a5304001qltv8vTWi6oaZQ","sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","type":"tool","tool":"bash","callID":"toolu_8ae5499e118d4a1cbfe72413","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"command":"ls -la /home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/pkg/apis/runtime/","description":"List runtime API directory structure"},"output":"total 16\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:43 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:37 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  861 Apr 11 00:43 register.go\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:44 v1alpha1\n","metadata":{"output":"total 16\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:43 .\ndrwxr-xr-x 3 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:37 ..\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root  861 Apr 11 00:43 register.go\ndrwxr-xr-x 2 root root 4096 Apr 11 00:44 v1alpha1\n","exit":0,"description":"List runtime API directory structure","truncated":false},"title":"List runtime API directory structure","time":{"start":1775839635599,"end":1775839635611}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775839635617,"sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","part":{"id":"prt_d784a5cf1001Rw8880iKdjX09F","messageID":"msg_d784a5304001qltv8vTWi6oaZQ","sessionID":"ses_287b61ae9ffeRwGS11QpcSqa0Z","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_10ec3b36cb6447cebdbdc22c","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage AI agent runtime configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing the foundation for sandbox orchestration and lifecycle management.\n6: \n7: The `AgentRuntime` resource represents a configurable agent execution environment with support for:\n8: - Code interpreter attachment\n9: - Resource quotas (CPU, memory, storage)\n10: - Network policies and egress rules\n11: - Lifecycle hooks (preStart, postStop)\n12: - Status tracking (phase, conditions, sandbox reference)\n13: \n14: ## Scope\n15: \n16: **Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n17: **API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n18: **Kind:** `AgentRuntime` (namespaced)  \n19: **Size:** S\n20: \n21: ### In Scope\n22: \n23: 1. **Type Definitions** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/types.go`)\n24:    - `AgentRuntime` - main resource struct\n25:    - `AgentRuntimeSpec` - desired state specification\n26:    - `AgentRuntimeStatus` - observed state status\n27:    - `CodeInterpreterSpec` - embedded code interpreter configuration\n28:    - `ResourceQuota` - sandbox resource limits\n29:    - `NetworkPolicy` - egress/ingress rules\n30:    - `LifecycleHook` - preStart/postStop callbacks\n31:    - `AgentRuntimePhase` - lifecycle phase enum\n32:    - `AgentRuntimeCondition` - status conditions\n33: \n34: 2. **API Registration** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/register.go`)\n35:    - `SchemeGroupVersion` definition\n36:    - `SchemeBuilder` registration\n37:    - `AddToScheme` function\n38:    - `Resource` and `Kind` helpers\n39: \n40: 3. **CRD Manifest** (`manifests/charts/base/crds/agentruntime.yaml`)\n41:    - OpenAPI v3 schema validation\n42:    - Subresources: `/status`, `/scale` (if needed)\n43:    - AdditionalPrinterColumns for kubectl output\n44:    - Conversion webhook placeholders (future)\n45: \n46: 4. **Defaulting & Validation** (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/defaults.go`, `validation.go`)\n47:    - `SetDefaults_AgentRuntime` - default values\n48:    - `ValidateAgentRuntime` - spec validation rules\n49:    - `ValidateAgentRuntimeStatusUpdate` - status update validation\n50: \n51: 5. **Utility Functions**\n52:    - Phase transition helpers\n53:    - Condition management (GetCondition, SetCondition, RemoveCondition)\n54:    - Deep copy utilities (via code generation)\n55: \n56: ### Out of Scope\n57: \n58: - Controller implementation (covered by AR-002)\n59: - Webhook admission controllers (deferred to AR-010)\n60: - Conversion webhooks for version upgrades (deferred)\n61: - CLI commands for AgentRuntime (Python SDK task)\n62: \n63: ## Impact Analysis\n64: \n65: ### Dependencies\n66: \n67: | Dependency | Type | Reason |\n68: |------------|------|--------|\n69: | `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Required | MetaV1 types, runtime.Object, schema |\n70: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Required | ResourceList, PodSecurityContext, EnvVar |\n71: | `k8s.io/client-go` | Generated | Clientset, listers, informers (via `make gen-client`) |\n72: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis` | Module | API group registration |\n73: \n74: ### Downstream Consumers\n75: \n76: 1. **Controller (AR-002)**: Watches `AgentRuntime` resources, reconciles to create sandbox pods\n77: 2. **Router**: Reads `AgentRuntime` status to route traffic to active sandboxes\n78: 3. **Python SDK**: Provides high-level API for creating/managing AgentRuntime resources\n79: 4. **CLI Tool**: Exposes `agentcube runtime create/get/list/delete` commands\n80: 5. **Helm Chart**: Ships CRD manifest for cluster installation\n81: \n82: ### Breaking Changes\n83: \n84: None - this is the initial definition of the API.\n85: \n86: ### Migration Path\n87: \n88: Not applicable for initial implementation. Future version migrations (v1alpha2, v1beta1) will require:\n89: - Conversion webhook implementation\n90: - Storage version bumps\n91: - helm chart upgrade hooks\n92: \n93: ## Alternatives Considered\n94: \n95: ### Alternative 1: Use Deployment + ConfigMap instead of CRD\n96: \n97: **Approach:** Represent agent runtimes as standard Kubernetes Deployments with configuration in ConfigMaps.\n98: \n99: **Pros:**\n100: - No CRD complexity or controller required\n101: - Leverages built-in Kubernetes primitives\n102: - Simpler RBAC story\n103: \n104: **Cons:**\n105: - Loses semantic meaning (Deployment is generic)\n106: - Complex validation logic in admission webhooks\n107: - Status reporting requires custom annotations\n108: - Harder to query/filter agent-specific resources\n109: - No custom subresources (e.g., `/exec`, `/logs` future extensions)\n110: \n111: **Decision:** Rejected. CRD provides better abstraction, type safety, and extensibility for AgentCube semantics.\n112: \n113: ### Alternative 2: Single monolithic AgentRuntime CRD with all features\n114: \n115: **Approach:** Include all possible configuration options (networking, storage, auth, scheduling) in one large spec.\n116: \n117: **Pros:**\n118: - One resource to rule them all\n119: - Maximum flexibility for users\n120: \n121: **Cons:**\n122: - High cognitive load for simple use cases\n123: - Validation complexity\n124: - Harder to evolve individual aspects\n125: - Violates separation of concerns\n126: \n127: **Decision:** Rejected. Prefer composable design with `CodeInterpreter` as separate but related resource. Core `AgentRuntime` focuses on execution environment; advanced features (distributed training, multi-agent orchestration) can be future extensions.\n128: \n129: ### Alternative 3: Use Pod-level primitives (PodTemplate) directly\n130: \n131: **Approach:** Embed raw PodTemplateSpec in AgentRuntime spec.\n132: \n133: **Pros:**\n134: - Full Kubernetes pod configuration available\n135: - No translation layer needed\n136: \n137: **Cons:**\n138: - Exposes low-level K8s details to end users\n139: - Harder to enforce platform policies\n140: - Breaks abstraction if K8s pod spec changes\n141: \n142: **Decision:** Partially adopted. AgentRuntimeSpec contains a simplified `Container` subset (image, env, resources) rather than full PodSpec, with controller translating to Pod internals. This balances flexibility with abstraction.\n143: \n144: ## Implementation Plan\n145: \n146: 1. **Scaffold directory structure**\n147:    - `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`\n148:    - `pkg/apis/runtime/register.go` (group registration)\n149: \n150: 2. **Define Go types** (`types.go`)\n151:    - Core structs with JSON tags\n152:    - Phase enum and conditions\n153:    - Embedded CodeInterpreterSpec\n154: \n155: 3. **Implement registration** (`register.go`)\n156:    - SchemeGroupVersion constants\n157:    - SchemeBuilder wiring\n158: \n159: 4. **Add defaults and validation**\n160:    - `defaults.go`: SetDefaults_AgentRuntime\n161:    - `validation.go`: ValidateAgentRuntime\n162: \n163: 5. **Generate CRD manifest**\n164:    - Run `make gen-crd` (controller-gen)\n165:    - Place in `manifests/charts/base/crds/`\n166: \n167: 6. **Generate client code**\n168:    - Run `make gen-client` (code-generator)\n169:    - Produces clientset, listers, informers\n170: \n171: 7. **Write unit tests**\n172:    - Type round-trip serialization\n173:    - Defaulting behavior\n174:    - Validation rules\n175: \n176: ## Success Criteria\n177: \n178: - [ ] `AgentRuntime` CRD installs via Helm chart\n179: - [ ] `kubectl apply -f agentruntime.yaml` succeeds\n180: - [ ] `kubectl get agentruntime` shows custom columns\n181: - [ ] Go client can create/get/update AgentRuntime\n182: - [ ] Spec validation rejects invalid resources\n183: - [ ] Defaulting applies expected values\n184: - [ ] Code generation produces compilable client-go code\n185: \n186: ## References\n187: \n188: - [Kubernetes API Conventions](https://git.k8s.io/community/contributors/devel/sig-architecture/api-conventions.md)\n189: - [Controller Tools CRD Generation](https://book.kubebuilder.io/reference/markers/crd.html)\n190: - [Kubernetes Code Generator](https://github.com/kubernetes/code-generator)\n191: - AgentCube deployment spec: `deployment/spec.md`\n192: - Client-go reference: `deployment/client-go.md`\n\n(End of file - total 192 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: AR-001 — CRD AgentRuntime 类型定义\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the `AgentRuntime` Custom Resource Definition (CRD) and associated types for the AgentCube platform. This CRD enables users to declare and manage AI agent runtime configurations as Kubernetes-native resources, providing the foundation for sandbox orchestration and lifecycle management.\n\nThe `AgentRuntime` resource represents a configurable agent execution environment with support for:\n- Code interpreter attachment\n- Resource quotas (CPU, memory, storage)\n- Network policies and egress rules\n- Lifecycle hooks (preStart, postStop)\n- Status tracking (phase, conditions, sandbox reference)\n\n## Scope\n\n**Module:** `pkg/apis`  \n**API Group:** `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1`  \n**Kind:** `AgentRuntime` (namespaced)  \n**Size:** S\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-001/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775839635595,"end":1775839635614}}}}
